 This stately, five-bedroom residence in old-moneyed Westcliff, one of Johannesburg’s oldest and most expensive suburbs, is situated close to a number of Johannesburg’s top schools and within easy reach of both the Rosebank and Sandton CBDs. The home boasts a dramatic double-volume entrance foyer and expansive living, dining and entertainment areas.  The Cape winelands town of Paarl has in recent years become popular among Gauteng and KwaZulu Natal families because of the town’s excellent public schools. This gracious family home, ideally positioned between Paarl Girls’ High and Boys’ High, offers four bedrooms and three bathrooms. Special features include three fireplaces, as well as a designer kitchen, braai room and garage for four vehicles.